=== read_rows is bucketed per normalized query hash ===
--- pattern A, first query (7 read rows) is within the per-pattern limit ---
allowed
--- pattern A, second query (14 > 10) exceeds the limit of its own bucket ---
QUOTA_EXCEEDED
--- pattern B (a different query pattern) has its own bucket and is still allowed ---
allowed
=== result_rows is bucketed per normalized query hash ===
--- pattern A, first query (7 result rows) is within the per-pattern limit ---
allowed
--- pattern A, second query (14 > 10) exceeds the limit of its own bucket ---
QUOTA_EXCEEDED
--- pattern B (a different query pattern) has its own bucket and is still allowed ---
allowed
=== written_bytes is bucketed per normalized query hash ===
--- pattern A, first insert (7 rows = 56 bytes) is within the per-pattern limit ---
allowed
--- pattern A, second insert (cumulative 160 > 80) exceeds the limit of its own bucket ---
QUOTA_EXCEEDED
--- pattern B (a different query pattern) has its own bucket and is still allowed ---
allowed
=== errors are bucketed per normalized query hash ===
--- pattern A: the error bucket is exceeded, so the next query of the same pattern is rejected up-front ---
QUOTA_EXCEEDED
--- pattern B (a different query pattern) has its own error bucket and is still allowed ---
allowed
